Selenium class 8

Implicit wait:
will be applied for findElement() method

Explicit wait:
used to tel the webdriver to wait for a certain condition before throwing an exception fro a specified condition

Explicit wait works with ExpectedConditions class and waits until certain conditions are met or the given time is achieved

* sign in xpath is a wild card which can identify any tagname
//*[contains(text(), "Welcom')]

Fluent WAIT --> global wait
it is used to tell the webdriver to wait for certain condition as well as its frequency before throwing an exception

Implicit wait = waits to locate the element
Explicit wait = waits until certain condition
Fluent wait = sets timeouts, polling and ignores needed exceptions

WebTables:
WebTables are elements on the webpage, which are constracted by having rows and coloms

Types :
1. Static
2. Dynamic

WebTables consist of different sections or parts

<Table>
     <head>
            <tr>
                 <th></th>--column data or heading
            </tr>
     </thead>
     <tbody>
            <tr>
                 <td></td> -- table data
            </tr>
     </tbody>
</table>



